SUSY SUSY LATTICE is parallel code for RHMC simulations of extended-supersymmetric
Yang--Mills theories in two and four dimensions, including related measurements.
This package evolved from the MILC code, and supersedes the serial C++ code
presented in arXiv:1108.1503.

See subdirectories for more detailed READMEs:
2dSYM -- Two-dimensional N=(2,2) supersymmetric Yang--Mills theory
4dSYM -- Four-dimensional N=4 supersymmetric Yang--Mills theory

Feel free to contact David Schaich with any questions, requests for new
features, or (especially) bug reports:
http://dschaich.expressions.syr.edu

Authors:
Thomas DeGrand (University of Colorado Boulder)
David Schaich (Syracuse University)

Reference:
A summary of useful information appears in the following paper, which we ask
that you cite if you find SUSY LATTICE useful in your work:

David Schaich and Thomas DeGrand, "Parallel software for lattice N=4
supersymmetric Yang--Mills theory", http://arxiv.org/abs/1410.6971 (2014).

Development was supported in part by the U.S. Department of Energy under grants
DE-FG02-04ER41290, DE-SC0010005, DE-SC0008669 and DE-SC0009998.
